    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-15T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-15T22:00:00-05:00" n="648"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d648">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12927: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-16T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 16, 1935—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 16—6:01 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. Legation’s 21, January 16, 10 a.m. Following from American Consul at Hankow:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“January 15, 5 p.m. No information Szechwan developments. I telegraphed
                            General Liu Hsiang today giving names of places where Americans reside
                            in Szechwan and requesting information whether any of those places
                            dangerous for Americans in order that I may inform them accordingly. I
                            also requested him to instruct by telegraph local authorities to protect
                            Americans and insure their safe conduct to places of safety should it
                            become necessary for them to leave.</p>
                        <p>I am sending by air mail third warning letter to one American in each
                            mission station and institution in Szechwan outside Chungking. Warning
                            telegrams sent to Suifu, Nanki and Kiangtsing.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0779" n="667" xml:id="pg_667"/>
                <p>U.S.S. <hi rend="italic">Palos</hi> Chungking reports January 15 that general
                    opinion there is less pessimistic.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
